        Result: some form of document fingerprint. This should represent the HTTP payload only for HTTP captured resources. It may represent an MD5, a SHA1, and may be a fragment of the full representation of the digest.

      • flagDuplicateDigest

        public void flagDuplicateDigest(CaptureSearchResult payload)
        Mark this capture as a revisit of previous capture payload, identified by content digest.

        Record location information is copied from payload so that the content can be loaded from the record later.

        ResourceIndex implementations should call this method before returning CaptureSearchResults to AccessPoint.

        Parameters:
        payload - capture being revisited
        See Also:
        getDuplicateDigestStoredTimestamp(), getDuplicateDigestStoredDate(), getDuplicatePayloadFile(), getDuplicatePayloadOffset(), getDuplicatePayloadCompressedLength()

      • isDuplicateDigest

        public boolean isDuplicateDigest()
        whether this capture is a re-fetch of previously archived capture (revisit), detected by content's digest, and replay of that previous capture is not blocked.

        1.8.1 2014-10-02 behavior change. This method now returns false even for revisits, if the original capture is blocked. Use #isRevisitDigest() for old behavior.

        Returns:
        true if revisit

      • isRevisitDigest

        public boolean isRevisitDigest()
        whether this capture is a re-fetch of previously archived capture (revisit), detected by content's digest.

        This method is meant for use by replay processing. For use in user interface / web API code, consider isDuplicateDigest() is more appropriate.

        Returns:
        true if revisit

        public boolean isRobotFlagSet(String flag)
